##8 people from 2 Families Return to Beijing from Italy, 4 confirmed! The police have filed a report

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Recently, the overseas new crown pneumonia epidemic situation continues to spread, some countries epidemic situation is severe. Under the new situation that the risk of epidemic prevention and control of port has increased sharply, port has become the main battlefield of epidemic prevention and control.

According to the Beijing Municipal Public Security Bureau, on March 4,2020, a group of eight from Liao's family, including Liao's family and Liao's family, arrived in the Beijing Capital International Airport by plane from Italy. Among them, Liao mou-jun, Liao mou-hai and other 4 people were confirmed as new cases of pneumonia in Beijing.

It is worth noting that Liao and his family members were investigated by the Shunyi District Public Security Bureau in accordance with the law for using drugs to lower the temperature and lower the fever before boarding the plane, and for not filling in the health declaration card truthfully.

Take Medicine to reduce fever before boarding, fill in false information..

Open a case!

According to the investigation, Liao mou-jun and Liao mou-hai Department of sister-brother relations, and his family in Italy long-term business.

Since late February, Liao mou-jun, Liao mou-hai have fever, dry cough and other symptoms, before boarding the use of drugs to reduce fever temperature. There is a risk of infection among people in the same plane due to misfilling the health declaration card of the People's Republic of China.

On March 6, the Shunyi District Public Security Bureau opened a case for investigation in accordance with the law on suspicion of obstructing the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases.

The Beijing police will closely rely on the capital's strict management of the joint prevention, control and coordination mechanism, and will work with the relevant departments to build a tight defense line against the importation of infectious diseases outside the territory, and for illegal and criminal acts such as refusing to implement measures for the prevention and control of infectious diseases, will be dealt with in accordance with the law.

At a press conference on the afternoon of March 7, Gao Xiaojun, a spokesman for the Beijing Municipal Commission of Health, said that as of 2400 hours on March 6, Beijing had imported 11 confirmed cases, including 8 from Italy and 3 from Iran.

The case was included in two imported cases in the new outbreak of pneumonia announced in Beijing on the morning of March 4.

On March 5, there were 4 new confirmed cases of pneumonia in Beijing, which were imported cases from Italy.

Immigration officers will be punished if there is any false report!

Shanghai is on the move

According to a report by Xinhua News Agency, in view of the development trend of the new coronavirus pneumonia epidemic, the Shanghai Customs announced at a news conference held on the 7th in Shanghai on the prevention and control of the new coronavirus pneumonia epidemic, a 100% epidemiological investigation will be carried out on the entry of persons from countries (regions) where the epidemic is serious, and strict precautions will be taken against the risk of importation of the epidemic outside the country.

Komohara, deputy head of Shanghai Customs, said at the press conference that under the new situation that the risk of epidemic prevention and control at the ports has increased sharply, the ports have become the main battlefield of epidemic prevention and control. Shanghai customs will launch 100% epidemiological investigation on personnel from countries (regions) with severe epidemic situation. More than 300 professionals have been deployed to reinforce the scene at the port.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photograph: Shanghai Municipal People's Government

In order to meet the needs of epidemic prevention and control, the Shanghai Customs has formulated the procedures for the diversion and disposal of entry-level personnel at ports, readjusted and optimized the layout of ports, expanded the spatial layout of quarantine areas, reengineered the customs clearance procedures, and effectively responded to the evacuation of large passenger flows, ensure 100% epidemiological investigation is carried out smoothly.

Komohara stressed that the Shanghai customs urged transport operators to strictly implement measures such as reporting of abnormal conditions, quarantine broadcasting and publicity, and issued the guidelines on administrative punishment for passengers entering or leaving the country who are involved in the new pneumonia epidemic, which severely punished cheating, to Guide the vast number of inbound and outbound travellers to make a truthful health declaration.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"It is a legal obligation for the entry and exit personnel to declare truthfully, and if the entry and exit personnel conceal or falsely declare, resulting in the spread of the epidemic, they will be held responsible according to law, " Komohara said.

The Shanghai Customs has also added a crew chief reporting system, strengthened the reporting responsibility of airlines on their own initiative, and implemented a "zero reporting" system, requiring the crew chief of a flight to report items clearly listed by the customs before landing the flight, report the situation to the customs.

Shanghai Customs has upgraded its temperature measuring equipment at the airport port and added a warning function for low temperature exceeding range.

Komohara said that while striving not to miss any key passengers who need to be concentrated in isolation or isolated at home, the customs pays attention to humanized management, accelerating quarantine clearance to the maximum extent possible, and ensuring normal customs clearance order at the ports, all efforts should be made to solve the problem of excessive length of stay at passenger ports.

On March 2 and 3, the Shanghai Pudong International Airport found four positive nucleic acid tests among incoming passengers who had transferred from Iran, and handed them over to local disease control authorities to be confirmed as new cases of coronavirus pneumonia.

Importation of epidemic situation outside China

How big is the risk, and where does it come from?

China's epidemic prevention and control effect is gradually showing, but overseas is constantly sounding new alarm, which makes China's risk of imported epidemic situation become an urgent issue.

How big is the risk of overseas import? Where does it come from? On March 6, the Global Times carried out an investigation.

Italy

Li Na is one of more than 200,000 Chinese, mostly from Lishui and Wenzhou, who are reported to have set up clothing factories or run restaurants, bars and other services in Italy. She told the Global Times that she did not know many people from Zhejiang, Italy, who had returned home because of the epidemic, "but many who intend to return home or have already booked flights. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Italian medics work in tents set up outside a hospital in Brescia, Italy (photo: Xinhua)

Many places in Zhejiang have begun to exercise strict control over returned Chinese and overseas Chinese. Li Na, who has no plans to return to China, has been told by his hometown of Wencheng County, Wenzhou, that he will need to make a health declaration if he returns to China, and that he will need to be quarantined once he enters the country.

Lishui, next door to Wenzhou, is not relaxing either. Officials in the city of Qingtian said Qingtian would take the same measures for all returning youths from overseas, no matter which country they came from, as it did for returning youths from the affected areas in their home country -- Foshan -- to be sent to a medical observation point in the county for 14 days.

Iran

As early as February 26, an imported case from Iran was discovered in Ningxia. On March 5, there were 11 new confirmed cases imported from Iran in Gansu and one new case in Shanghai.

Zhang Ming, under a pseudonym, was one of the Chinese who returned to China on March 4 on a chartered flight from China. He said he was living and studying in Qom, the worst affected region in Iran, and that as more and more deaths were reported, he became increasingly worried about the level of medical care and facilities in the country.

In Iran, mask prices have skyrocketed, he said, and an N95 mask costs almost as much as an Iranian person can earn in a weekday. Due to the suspension of direct flights between Iran and China, returning from Iran to China requires a connecting flight, and the usual route is via Russia or Thailand.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A man wears a mask as he travels in Tehran, Iran, March 2,2010.

(photo: Xinhua News Agency, Photo by Ahmad)

Korea

In South Korea, where the outbreak is severe, a local Chinese told the Global Times that he had no plans to return home for the time being because "returning home means losing his job. ". Foreigners are often among the first to be laid off because of the epidemic and the loss of jobs, and they may consider leaving South Korea to return home, he said.

It is understood that some Chinese do want to return home in South Korea, including employees of chinese-owned enterprises, live broadcast in South Korea, such as Chinese people selling things. At present, those returning from South Korea are placed in isolation for a period of 14 days. Key cities such as Yantai, Dalian, Yanji and Qingdao have already taken targeted measures.

Workers Spray disinfectant in Daegu International Airport, South Korea, March 6,2010. (photo: Xinhua News Agency)

Japan

Lee, a Tokyo office worker, told reporters that Japan's response to the new pneumonia was not strong and that the government, the media and the public initially did not take it seriously, like "things from other countries. ". As the epidemic became more severe, companies began to implement measures such as working from home, "but it was too late. ". She was worried, but because of her job, she was unable to make the decision to resign and return home.

In general, unlike in Iran, the vast majority of Chinese in Japan will not return home in the near future, said Oishi, director of the Toyama Health Research Institute. Those who are willing to return to China are those who are staying for a short period of time and have been picked up by a chartered plane arranged by the embassy. Japan will begin mandatory quarantine of all Chinese visitors next week. China has also imposed quarantine restrictions on travelers from Japan. In addition, there has been a significant reduction in the number of people and flights between China and Japan during this period.

France, the United States and other countries, epidemic potential risk is difficult to estimate

Among the European and American countries, France, Germany, Spain and the United States are considered to be the countries where the recent epidemic situation has been aggravated obviously. Cao Huaqin, a Fujian businessman who lives in France, said, "As far as I know, not many Chinese in France want to return home because of the epidemic. The Chinese here are also very alert. Many people have bought rice, water and daily necessities for three months and try not to go out. "

Cao Huaqin said, "The overall level of health care in France is very advanced, and at the moment the deaths are only among elderly people with other diseases. The Chinese are more confident that if they get sick they can be cured, so there is no situation like in Italy. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The shelves of Pasta and Rice at a large supermarket chain in northern Paris, France, are strewn with leftovers on March 5. (photo: Xinhua News Agency reporter, Gao Jing)

Chinese in the United States said they had not heard of any plans to return home in the near future, because many flights have been canceled, but also worried about being infected during the flight. Still, the evolution of the epidemic in the United States deserves continued attention.

According to a report by The New York Times on the 5th, among the confirmed cases in the United States, 43 were from the "Diamond Princess" cruise ship, 15 had a history of travel in China, 11 had a history of travel in Italy, and 2 had a history of travel in Egypt, one with a history of travel to Korea or Iran.

Expert: It is critical to quickly identify risks at entry points

Wang Peiyu, deputy dean of the Public Health at Peking University, said that in addition to the above countries, there are other countries that need more attention, such as Kuwait and Bahrain in the Middle East, based on the number of flights with China and the epidemic there, thailand and Cambodia in Asia and parts of Europe.

From February 25 to March 3, airports in Beijing, Qingdao, Shanghai, Shenyang and Yanji had the highest number of flights to China from South Korea, according to another report, shanghai, Beijing, Guangzhou and Dalian are the top destinations for flights from Japan to China, while Shanghai, Beijing and Shenyang are the top destinations in the United States.

According to Wang Peiyu, there are two main ways to prevent imported cases, one is to carry out strict temperature testing and travel history investigation and registration upon entry, the other is to call on citizens to reduce travel to countries with high epidemic incidence and risk.

Sources: Ping An, Beijing, Xinhua, Shanghai Municipal People's Government, Global Times, etc.
